<h1 class="h1">How to Install Python (Environment Set-up)</h1>
<p>In order to become Python developer, the first step is to learn how to install or update Python on a local machine or computer. In this tutorial, we will discuss the installation of Python on various operating systems. </p>
<h2 class="h2">Installation on Windows</h2>
<p>Visit the link <a href="https://www.python.org/downloads/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow"><em>https://www.python.org/downloads/</em></a> to download the latest release of <a href="https://www.javatpoint.com/python-tutorial">Python</a>. In this process, we will install Python 3.8.6 on our <a href="https://www.javatpoint.com/windows">Windows operating system</a>. When we click on the above link, it will bring us the following page.</p>
<p><strong>Step - 1: Select the Python's version to download.</strong></p>
<p>Click on the download button.</p>
<img src="https://static.javatpoint.com/python/images/python-environment-set-up.png" alt="Python Environment Set-up" />
<p><strong>Step - 2: Click on the Install Now</strong></p>
<p>Double-click the executable file, which is downloaded; the following window will open. Select Customize installation and proceed. Click on the Add Path check box, it will set the Python path automatically.</p>
<img src="https://static.javatpoint.com/python/images/python-environment-set-up2.png" alt="Python Environment Set-up" />
<p>We can also click on the customize installation to choose desired location and features. Other important thing is install launcher for the all user must be checked.</p>
<p><strong>Step - 3 Installation in Process</strong></p>
<img src="https://static.javatpoint.com/python/images/python-environment-set-up3.png" alt="Python Environment Set-up" />
<p>Now, try to run python on the command prompt. Type the command python -version in case of python3.</p>
<img src="https://static.javatpoint.com/python/images/python-environment-set-up4.png" alt="Python Environment Set-up" />

<p>We are ready to work with the Python.</p>
